'''''Star Wars Insider'' 61''' is the sixty-first issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[August 6]], [[2002]]. This was the final ''Star Wars Insider'' issue published by [[Wizards of the Coast]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*From the Editor's Desk
*[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*[[Star News]]: From the World of Lucasfilm {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader Catalog]]
*[[Behind the Magic]] &mdash; Crouching Yoda, Hidden Dooku {{C|by [[Rob Coleman]]}}
*[[Gamescape]] &mdash; Strong in the Force {{C|by [[Brian Campbell]]}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; [[The New Jedi Order: Traitor|''Traitor'']] in the Ranks {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; A [[Marvel Comics|Marvelous]] Comeback {{C|by [[Abel G. Peña]]}}
*[[Set Piece]]: Cloud City Carbon-Freezing Chamber {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]] & [[Chris Reiff]]}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; Movie & Merchandise Wow! {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; A Man for the Millennium {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*[[The Last Page]] {{C|by [[Joy Stephens]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Inside Attack of the Clones|Inside ''Attack of the Clones'']]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>Dig into three more amazing scenes from ''Attack of the Clones'' with the ''Insider''{{'s}} resident archaeologist.</small>
*"[[John Williams: Across the Stars]]" {{C|by [[Brian J. Robb]]}}
*:<small>It just wouldn't be ''[[Star Wars]]'' without the music of [[John Williams]], and [[George Lucas]] wouldn't have it any other way.</small>
*"[[Star Wars Celebration II (article)|''Star Wars'' Celebration II]]" {{C|by [[Michael Mikaelian]] & [[Dave Gross]]}}
*:<small>Indianapolis was bursting at the seams May 3-5 with thousands of ''Star Wars'' fans like you. Here's your exclusive report.</small>
*"[[Rose Byrne: A Rose by Any Other Name]]" {{C|by [[Michael G. Ryan]]}}
*:<small>Australian actress [[Rose Byrne]] ([[Dormé/Legends|Dormé]]) relates her once-in-a-lifetime experience on the set of ''Attack of the Clones''.</small>
*"[[Veronica Segura: From Mexico to Naboo]]" {{C|by [[Dave Gross]], interview by [[Saul Arellano]] &mdash; reprinted from Mexican fan magazine}}
*:<small>Mexican actress [[Veronica Segura]] ([[Cordé/Legends|Cordé]]) struggled with the hardships of working on a ''Star Wars'' film—long hours, heavy costumes, and partial scripts—and loved every minute of it.</small>
*"[[Race Across the Dune Sea]]" {{C|by Michael G. Ryan}}
*:<small>[[Brennan Swain]] and [[Rob Frisbee]] not only won ''The Amazing Race'', they walked the sands of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]].</small>
*"[[The Beautiful Campaign: Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones at the 2002 World Cup|The Beautiful Campaign: ''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'' at the 2002 World Cup]]" {{C|by [[Michelle Vuckovich]]}}
*:<small>[[Podracing/Legends|Podracing]] it ain't, but this year [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] is strong with this ''planet''{{'s}} most popular sport.</small>
*"[[Sith Rising Card Encyclopedia|''Sith Rising'' Card Encyclopedia]]" {{C|by Michael G. Ryan}}
*:<small>The latest expansion set for the ''Star Wars'' Trading Card Game is coming. Here's your first look at all 90 cards in the regular set, with comments from the designers.</small>

